---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Pagination from "../../components/Pagination.astro";
import Picture from "../../components/Picture.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Kuali" pathname="/work/kuali/" caseStudy={true}>
  <div class="case-study">
    <div class="case-study-header">
      <div class="case-study-header-content constrain">
        <h1>Kuali</h1>
        <div class="case-study-header-nav">
          <a title="Previous" href="/work/balto/"
            ><Pagination name="previous" /></a
          >
          <a title="Next" href="/work/texas-state/"
            ><Pagination name="next" /></a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="case-study-overview">
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>My role:</strong> Product Designer
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>The problem:</strong> Higher education researchers and administrators,
          some managing decades of critical documentation, had no efficient way to
          surface records from a large and complex database. The legacy search interface
          was a single, rigid form that was sluggish and poorly suited to the diversity
          of institutions and roles.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Top outcome:</strong> A validated search and filtering system featuring
          customizable, saveable lookup views, tested with real clients, giving users
          precision control over their records.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="case-study-content">
      <h2>Context and scope</h2>
      <p>
        Kuali builds software for higher education institutions, serving
        researchers, compliance teams, students, and faculty. I was the primary
        designer for the <em>Research</em> product, embedded with a product manager and
        roughly a dozen engineers in a matrix organization where each designer
        owned a dedicated product line.
      </p>
      <p>
        My work spanned the entire design process: user interviews, concept
        sketching, high-fidelity prototyping, and production CSS. I also
        contributed to a cross-product initiative to unify the platform’s
        navigation and design system.
      </p>
      <h2>Execution</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Discovery:</strong> Conducted recorded user interviews with stakeholders
          and end users to document pain points, existing workarounds, and workflow
          edge cases across multiple institutions and departments.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Concept development:</strong> Explored multiple low-fidelity approaches,
          landing on a dual-mode solution: a traditional omnibar for power users and
          a custom lookup builder allowing users to define, save, and share targeted
          views of the database.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Validation:</strong> Ran iterative testing sessions with real users,
          documenting feedback across rounds. The custom lookup concept landed well
          with participants, particularly the ability for product owners to deploy
          role-specific views to their teams.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Platform extension:</strong> The document finder's universal search
          patterns sparked a broader initiative with the design team, resulting in
          high-fidelity designs for a shared navigation system, global search, and
          co-branding framework addressing long-standing requests from multi-product
          customers.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="case-study-visuals pswp-gallery">
      <Picture
        name="kuali-browser"
        alt="Product shot, system search"
        class="case-study-visuals-browser"
        loading="eager"
        lightbox
        fetchpriority="high"
      />
      <Picture
        name="kuali-find-results"
        alt="Sketch, find documents with results"
        lightbox
      />
      <Picture
        name="kuali-find-columns"
        alt="Sketch, show and hide columns dialog"
        lightbox
      />
      <Picture
        name="kuali-find-searches"
        alt="Sketch, saved searches slide-out sidebar"
        lightbox
      />
      <Picture
        name="kuali-find-builder"
        alt="Sketch, find documents custom form builder"
        lightbox
      />
      <Picture name="kuali-find" alt="Product shot, find documents" lightbox />
      <Picture
        name="kuali-apps"
        alt="Product shot, application switcher"
        lightbox
      />
      <Picture name="kuali-nav" alt="Product shot, main navigation" lightbox />
      <Picture name="kuali-cobrand" alt="Product shot, co-branding" lightbox />
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
